\"5fe98893\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Sala Luxuty - Palatul Noblesse\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTE1MjYsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wNFwvU2FsYS1MdXh1dHktUGFsYXR1bC1Ob2JsZXNzZS5qcGciLCJzbGlkZXNob3ciOiI1ZmU5ODg5MyJ9\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/showroom-noblesse-interiors-sala-luxury-palatul-noblesse.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"5fe98893\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"showroom-noblesse-interiors-sala-luxury-palatul-noblesse\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTE1MjMsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wNFwvc2hvd3Jvb20tbm9ibGVzc2UtaW50ZXJpb3JzLXNhbGEtbHV4dXJ5LXBhbGF0dWwtbm9ibGVzc2UuanBnIiwic2xpZGVzaG93IjoiNWZlOTg4OTMifQ%3D%3D\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t<p><em>Stuccoes – original</em><br /><em>Carpentry – original</em><br /><em>Flooring – marble in a combination of white and black, a geometric pattern created using the “water-jet” technique</em><br /><em>Artworks – contemporary artists, <a href=\\"https://fusionarts.ro/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Fusion Arts</a> portfolio</em><br /><em>Furniture pieces – <a href=\\"https://www.noblesseinteriors.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Noblesse Interiors</a> portfolio</em></p><p><strong>When it comes to organizing events in Bucharest, Noblesse Palace offers, in addition to a versatile setting, a full range of services such as: dedicated event manager, event design, personalized menus, floral arrangements, photo-video services, entertainment, guided tour of the palace, piano rental from 1800, refurbished and in perfect condition, and many more.</strong><br /><strong>Moreover, we organize a wide range of events, from art exhibitions and fairs to private and corporate events, as well as charitable events.</strong></p>", "meta_desc": "The Luxury Hall is located to the right of the central hallway and, as the name suggests, is adorned with many luxury pieces", "date": "2024-04-15 13:30:03"},{"id": 12163, "title": "Baroque Hall", "slug": "baroque-hall", "parent_id": 12010, "parent_slug": "ground-floor", "type": "page", "content": "<h2>The most imposing hall of Noblesse Palace, named after the predominant style that characterizes it, the Baroque Hall emerges at the end of the entrance hallway</h2>\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t<p>At the end of the central hallway, behind the beautifully decorated fir doors, elegance and unique charm unfold as the Baroque Hall. Once a witness to era-defining balls, enlivened by music and dance, this room faded into obscurity during the communist regime, only to be revived in modern days as the central hall of Noblesse Palace.<br />The centerpiece of this room is the ceiling painting, a breathtaking masterpiece that commands attention. Utilizing the \\"trompe l'oeil\\" technique to create fictitious volume and depth, it features architectural elements in perspective, allegorically personifying muses such as literature, painting, theater, music, as well as mystical characters. This artwork is the creation of the painter <a href=\\"https://www.facebook.com/septimiu.capatina.5\\">Septimiu Căpățînă</a>. The sensation is unparalleled; the composition begins with the paintings in the central hall and continues onto the ceiling of the Baroque Hall, reaching into the clouds in an idyllic setting that brings us close to Eden.<br />The original stuccoes on the ceiling, covered by layers of paint in vain attempts to conceal their brilliance, are rediscovered today after three months of intense cleaning, polishing, and specific treatments carried out by a team of skilled plasterers.<br />Another special element of the Baroque Hall is the floor, composed of over 3500 pieces of marble, assembled manually, captivating at first sight and astonishing with its unexpected interplay of colors and shapes, conceived as a mirror to the salon's ceiling.<br />Beautiful as a museum piece, a white terracotta stove, expertly restored, stands watch like a secular witness from its corner, having undoubtedly heard countless life stories. And to complete the regal ambiance, just like in an ancient ballroom, an immense crystal and golden bronze chandelier reigns in the center, bathing the entire room in light, ready to receive its guests. And worthy of such grandeur, we have carefully selected valuable furniture pieces, in Baroque and Empire styles, to further adorn this main chamber, as well as a fully restored 1800s piano, enchanting the ears and souls of our guests today.<br />The Baroque Hall can be rented for conferences, courses, concerts, performances, private events, weddings, christenings, anniversary parties, corporate events, social events, company or product launches, filming, and much more. It has an area of 45 square meters, with an exit to a foyer-type terrace with an area of 12 square meters. It can accommodate up to 50 people in conference arrangement, 30 people in banquet arrangement, and 80 people in cocktail arrangement. It is equipped with sound system and projector, screen, flipchart, air conditioning, Wi-Fi. The Baroque Hall communicates with two other rooms located to the right and left, thus allowing for an increased number of guests.</p>\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Paltul-Noblesse-08.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"48d24666\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Sala Baroque\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTEwMTksInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wM1wvUGFsdHVsLU5vYmxlc3NlLTA4LmpwZyIsInNsaWRlc2hvdyI6IjQ4ZDI0NjY2In0%3D\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Palatul-Noblesse-16.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"48d24666\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Palatul Noblesse\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTEwMjUsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wM1wvUGFsYXR1bC1Ob2JsZXNzZS0xNi5qcGciLCJzbGlkZXNob3ciOiI0OGQyNDY2NiJ9\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/b09.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"48d24666\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"b09\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTE1MzEsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wNFwvYjA5LmpwZyIsInNsaWRlc2hvdyI6IjQ4ZDI0NjY2In0%3D\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Palatul-Noblesse-13.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"48d24666\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Palatul Noblesse\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTEwMTgsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wM1wvUGFsYXR1bC1Ob2JsZXNzZS0xMy5qcGciLCJzbGlkZXNob3ciOiI0OGQyNDY2NiJ9\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Palatul-Noblesse-04-1.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"48d24666\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Palatul Noblesse 04\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTEwMDksInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wM1wvUGFsYXR1bC1Ob2JsZXNzZS0wNC0xLmpwZyIsInNsaWRlc2hvdyI6IjQ4ZDI0NjY2In0%3D\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Tavanul.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"48d24666\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Tavanul\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTEwMjQsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wM1wvVGF2YW51bC5qcGciLCJzbGlkZXNob3ciOiI0OGQyNDY2NiJ9\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t<p><em>Stuccoes – original</em><br /><em>Carpentry – original</em><br /><em>White terracotta stove - original<br />Ceiling painting - Allegory of the Arts, created by <a href=\\"https://www.facebook.com/septimiu.capatina.5\\">Septimiu Căpățînă</a><br />Flooring – marble in a combination of white and black, a geometric pattern created using the “water-jet” technique</em><br /><em>Artworks – contemporary artists, <a href=\\"https://fusionarts.ro/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Fusion Arts</a> portfolio</em><br /><em>Furniture pieces – <a href=\\"https://www.noblesseinteriors.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Noblesse Interiors</a> portfolio</em></p><p><strong>When it comes to organizing events in Bucharest, Noblesse Palace offers, in addition to a versatile setting, a full range of services such as: dedicated event manager, event design, personalized menus, floral arrangements, photo-video services, entertainment, guided tour of the palace, piano rental from 1800, refurbished and in perfect condition, and many more.</strong><br /><strong>Moreover, we organize a wide range of events, from art exhibitions and fairs to private and corporate events, as well as charitable events.</strong></p>", "meta_desc": "The most imposing hall of Noblesse Palace, named after the predominant style that characterizes it, the Baroque Hall emerges at the end of the entrance hallway", "date": "2024-04-15 13:44:20"},{"id": 12168, "title": "Florence Hall", "slug": "florence-hall", "parent_id": 12010, "parent_slug": "ground-floor", "type": "page", "content": "<h2>The most imposing hall of Noblesse Palace, named after the predominant style that characterizes it, the Baroque Hall emerges at the end of the entrance hallway</h2>\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tFrom the Baroque Hall, through the wide open door on the left, you catch a glimpse of a room so ethereal, the Florence Hall, dressed in a warm cream color, with a marble floor in shades of white and cream, harmoniously intertwined like a chessboard. The ceiling, laden with stuccoes, has been left white, with only a golden patina and occasional silver accents contouring the delicate shapes of the stuccoes. For those who don't know, the ceiling of this room was completely demolished and a heavy slab was poured for strength. The rosette from the center of the ceiling was preserved, restored to its place after the consolidation work was completed. Most of the stuccoes were made in the Louis XV style, adorning both the ceiling and the side walls. Additionally, the walls of this room have been enriched with two niches made of plaster, giving a sense of depth.<br>The most valuable and oldest piece is the green terracotta stove, demolished and rebuilt piece by piece, so beautiful and imposing that it rightfully deserves the name of the hostess of this room.<br>And because it's called the Florence Hall, furniture from the Florence area, expertly crafted by Italian artisans, beautifully adorns the translucent white walls. The console carved with gold leaf, overseen by an imposing mirror, guards the wall in front of the room.<br>This room can be rented for conferences, courses, concerts, performances, private events, weddings, baptisms, anniversaries, corporate events, social events, launches, filming, and much more. It has an area of 32 square meters and can accommodate up to 30 people. It is equipped with a video projector, screen, flipchart, air conditioning, and Wi-Fi.\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Sala-Florence.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"32c78bdd\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Sala Florence\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTE1MzYsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wNFwvU2FsYS1GbG9yZW5jZS5qcGciLCJzbGlkZXNob3ciOiIzMmM3OGJkZCJ9\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Palatul-Noblesse-03.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"32c78bdd\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Palatul Noblesse 03\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTE1MzcsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wNFwvUGFsYXR1bC1Ob2JsZXNzZS0wMy5qcGciLCJzbGlkZXNob3ciOiIzMmM3OGJkZCJ9\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Sala-Florence-1.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"32c78bdd\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Sala Florence\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTE1MzgsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wNFwvU2FsYS1GbG9yZW5jZS0xLmpwZyIsInNsaWRlc2hvdyI6IjMyYzc4YmRkIn0%3D\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t<p><em>Stuccoes – original</em><br /><em>Carpentry – original</em><br /><em>Green terracotta stove - original</em><br /><em>Flooring – marble in a combination of white and cream, a geometric pattern created using the \\"water-jet\\" technique</em><br /><em>Artworks – contemporary artists, <a href=\\"https://fusionarts.ro/\\">Fusion Arts</a> portfolio</em><br /><em>Furniture pieces – <a href=\\"https://www.noblesseinteriors.com/\\">Noblesse Interiors</a> portfolio</em></p><p><strong>When it comes to organizing events in Bucharest, Palatul Noblesse offers, alongside a versatile setting, a complete range of services such as: dedicated event manager, event design, personalized menus, floral arrangements, photo-video services, entertainment, guided tours of the palace, rental of a piano from 1800, refurbished and in perfect condition, and much more. Additionally, we organize events of various kinds, from art exhibitions and fairs to private and corporate events, as well as charitable events.</strong></p>", "meta_desc": "The most imposing hall of Noblesse Palace, named after the predominant style that characterizes it, the Baroque Hall emerges at the end of...", "date": "2024-04-15 13:55:37"},{"id": 12173, "title": "Regent Hall", "slug": "regent-hall", "parent_id": 12010, "parent_slug": "ground-floor", "type": "page", "content": "<h2>To the right of the Baroque Hall, a new room opens up, different from all the others, the Regent Hall</h2>\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tTo the right of the Baroque hall, a new room opens up, different from all the others, the Regent hall. The walls are clad in walnut wood paneling, with golden profiles and decorations to give more weight to this hall. You can take a seat on welcoming sofas or on the leather armchair in front of the fireplace.<br>Elements from both the Louis XV and Louis XVI styles vie to show their beauty and supremacy. And from such an overwhelming battle of styles and influences, abound Chinese porcelain vases, busts and statuettes, old books and bronze candlesticks, albums, photo frames, and other decorations, along with a large tapestry on the wall, made in modern times to recreate a long-forgotten era.<br>It's an intimate room, intentionally designed so and carefully arranged to host smaller, private meetings or serve as a corner of refuge at major events. It has a separate entrance and a lavish bathroom.<br>The Regent hall can be rented separately for private discussions or business meetings, as well as for photo shoots or product presentations. The hall has an area of 24 square meters and can accommodate up to 14 people. It is equipped with a video projector, screen, flipchart, air conditioning, and Wi-Fi.\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Sala-Regent-1.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"5f7c0f3a\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Sala Regent\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTE1NDYsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wNFwvU2FsYS1SZWdlbnQtMS5qcGciLCJzbGlkZXNob3ciOiI1ZjdjMGYzYSJ9\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Sala-Regent-Palatul-Noblesse-1.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"yes\\" data-elementor-lightbox-slideshow=\\"5f7c0f3a\\" data-elementor-lightbox-title=\\"Sala Regent Palatul Noblesse\\" data-e-action-hash=\\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dlightbox%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6MTE1NDcsInVybCI6Imh0dHBzOlwvXC93d3cucGFsYXR1bG5vYmxlc3NlLnJvXC93cC1jb250ZW50XC91cGxvYWRzXC8yMDI0XC8wNFwvU2FsYS1SZWdlbnQtUGFsYXR1bC1Ob2JsZXNzZS0xLmpwZyIsInNsaWRlc2hvdyI6IjVmN2MwZjNhIn0%3D\\">\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t</a>\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<a href=\\"https://www.palatulnoblesse.ro/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Sala-Regent-Palatul-Noblesse-2.jpg\\" data-elementor-open-lightbox=\\"ye